hnson, 2000). Reduced PSII efficiency limits electron transfer from QA to QB, decreasing plastoquinone reduction and proton gradient formation across the thylakoid membrane, thereby constraining ATP and NADPH production (Broser et al., 2011). Because ATP and NADPH drive the Calvin&ndash;Benson cycle, impaired PSII function mechanistically results in decreased carbon fixation and overall photosynthetic rate.", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 15:33:41 +0000 2026"}